                "Desc": "In the year 2147 of the Light Calendar, the holy city faced the calamity of the black tide and faded into the night.<br>This tome chronicles the fallen and records the sorrow of Okhema.<br><br><b>Fallen Soldiers, Priests, and Scholars</b><br>...<br><br>• Alpheus and Malonza – Twin brothers who perished for the holy city.<br><br><br> / <br>• Petros – A valiant Mountain Dweller, his sacrifice immortal.<br><br><br> / <br>• Margusa - A wise researcher who unfortunately passed away at a market.<br><br><br> / <br>• Ulysse – A acolyte, perished while shielding companions.<br><br><br> / <br>• Nereia – A Kephale priest, her mission ended at her resting place.<br><br><b>Fallen Citizens</b><br>...<br><br>• Antigone – Daughter of Acacias, perished in a collapsed home.<br><br>• Theagis – A mother of three, perished embracing her youngest.<br><br><br> / <br>• Albus – A righteous man, passed away in prayer.<br><br><br> / <br>• Bolaris – A man of the people, perished facing the Black Tide Creatures.<br><br><br> / <br>• Hygilos – A merchant, found dead in his shop.<br><br><br> / <br>• Lucretia – A friend of the dromas, perished after fulfilling what should be done.<br><br><br> / <br>• Marcus – A weathered man, met his fate beyond Okhema.<br><br><br><br><br><b>Missing Persons</b><br>• Hegesia – A humble soul, missing.<br><br><b>Others</b><br>• Ten unidentified bodies, features unrecognizable.<br><br>...<br><br>May the grace of Thanatos guide these souls to a new world.<br>We shall meet again at the end of the west wind."
