        "World": 5,
        "Books": [
            {
                "Desc": "— A Hymn for the Chalice of Plenty<br><br>[Tuning Instructions]<br>Twelve strings correspond to the powers of the Twelve Titans:<br>1  Evernight - E   (String of Oronyx)<br>2  Justice - A   (String of Talanton)<br>3  Infinity - D   (String of Janus)<br>4 Twilight - G   (String of Aquila)<br>5  Pillar - C   (String of Georios)<br>6  Plenty - F   (String of Phagousa)<br>7  Worlds - B   (String of Kephale)<br>8 Rift - E'  (String of Cerces)<br>9  Gold - A'  (String of Mnestia)<br>10 Fury - D'  (String of Nikador)<br>11  Whimsy - G'  (String of Zagreus)<br>12  Shadow - C'  (String of Thanatos)<br><br><i>The lyre strings need to be doused in Phagousa's holy water for their divine powers to manifest</i><br><i>For every increased inch of water, their pitch rises half step</i><br><br>[First Movement: Rising]<br>Water level: Initial surge (Ankle height)<br>Cadence: ♩=72 Gentle as a morning tide<br><br>E  |-E---B---|C---E---|<br>A  |--A---C--|--E---G-|<br>D  |---D---E-|---G---B|<br>G  |----G----|----C---|<br>C  |-----C---|-----E--|<br>F  |------F--|------A-|<br>B  |---------|B---D---|<br>E' |---------|--E---G-|<br>A' |---------|---A----|<br>D' |---------|----D---|<br>G' |---------|-----G--|<br>C' |---------|------C-|<br><br>[Second Movement: Tidal Surge]<br>Water level: Crescendo (Knee height)<br>Cadence: ♩=108 Like a surging tide<br><br>E  |-E-B-E-|-G-B-E-|<br>A  |-A-C-E-|-C-E-A-|<br>D  |-D-E-G-|-E-G-D-|<br>G  |-G-B-D-|-B-D-G-|<br>C  |-C-E-G-|-E-G-C-|<br>F  |-F-A-C-|-A-C-F-|<br>B  |-B-D-F-|-D-F-B-|<br>E' |-E-G-B-|-G-B-E-|<br>A' |-A-C-E-|-C-E-A-|<br>D' |-D-F-A-|-F-A-D-|<br>G' |-G-B-D-|-B-D-G-|<br>C' |-C-E-G-|-E-G-C-|<br><br>Third Movement: Tidal Climax<br>Water level: Full (Chest height)<br>Cadence: ♩=144 Like a descending storm<br><br>E  |-E-G-B-E-|-B-E-G-B-|<br>A  |-A-C-E-A-|-C-E-A-C-|<br>D  |-D-F-A-D-|-F-A-D-F-|<br>G  |-G-B-D-G-|-B-D-G-B-|<br>C  |-C-E-G-C-|-E-G-C-E-|<br>F  |-F-A-C-F-|-A-C-F-A-|<br>B  |-B-D-F-B-|-D-F-B-D-|<br>E' |-E-G-B-E-|-G-B-E-G-|<br>A' |-A-C-E-A-|-C-E-A-C-|<br>D' |-D-F-A-D-|-F-A-D-F-|<br>G' |-G-B-D-G-|-B-D-G-B-|<br>C' |-C-E-G-C-|-E-G-C-E-|<br><br>Score Information<br>1. [-] indicates a fermata, one beat for every cell<br>2. The twelve-string tuning symbols indicate the base pitch, and actual pitch fluctuates according to water level<br>3. The score corresponds with the twelve strings' positions from top to bottom<br><br>Performance Notes<br>This score is only recorded with standard melodic phrases, and actual performance is influenced by the following factors:<br>   1. During the rising tide, the pitch naturally rises as well<br>   2. The timbre becomes more sonorous during quicker currents<br>    3. The harmony becomes richer when storms descend<br>   4. When a performance takes place along a coast, resonance is amplified<br><br>Special Performance Influences<br>   ≈ Wave Sounds: Produced during intense currents<br>   ↑ Rising Tide Sounds: Pitch rises with the water level<br>   ↓ Receding Tide Sounds: Pitch lowers with the water level<br>  ～ Afterecho: Persists as flow changes<br><br>[Reminder]<br>1. Please do not perform when during black tide disasters<br>2. Phagousa's holy water must be imbibed first before battle<br>3. Please protect the lyre from water when performing in storms<br>4. Beware of Zagreus' disciples who may secretly replace the lyre's strings"
            }
        ]
